_result_payload` carries `family = \"bernoulli_probit\"` with NO heritability field (liability scale) and `dispersion = nothing`; and a non-{0,1} response is guarded. LAPLACE ONLY ŌĆö the probit variational expected information is response-dependent (`ŌłÆE[ŌäōŌĆ│]` varies with `s = 2yŌłÆ1`), which the response-free `_fam_expected_weight` signature cannot carry, so `marginal = :variational` is rejected (a VA kernel is explicit follow-up). An opt-in seeded recovery harness (`sim/phase6_threshold_recovery.jl`, outside CI; checkpoint `docs/dev-log/recovery-checkpoints/2026-06-22-threshold-recovery.md`) on 5 pre-declared seeds (q = 345, liability-threshold DGP) passes the hard gate 5/5 (converged Ōł¦ interior Žā╠é┬▓a Ōł¦ EBV cor 0.61ŌĆō0.76), with the Žā╠é┬▓a MAGNITUDE REPORTED-NOT-GATED and DOWNWARD-biased as expected for binary data (3/5 within rel Ōēż 0.45; mean Žā╠é┬▓a 0.633 vs 1.0, ~37% downward) ŌĆö the documented Laplace-for-binary information effect (cf. `V6-BERNOULLI`; an ordinal Ōēź3-category design would be more informative).",
